race.comment: HE'S BON'S BOY (3) stalked the pace from a low draw last start and fought on well to finish 4.5 lengths away in third (30.41) at Wentworth Park in a Grade 5 over 520m. Form from his last run is proving strong. One of the contenders. SNOOPY'S ETHICS (1) turned in a better effort at Richmond Straight last start, finishing third behind Hear Me Roar (17.72) in a Grade 5. Chased the leaders and with a clean run can be prominent. Bold showing expected. ISLE OF LACHLAN (2) scored two back then was always well back and could manage only a 4.5 lengths 7th at Richmond Straight (17.57). Can do much better this time. CESSNOCK CURTAIN (8) jumps at a shorter distance and still warrants respect.
